result.adr_address: High St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: High St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.name: High Street Grill

reviews.text: A good and firm favourite after a few visits - friendly staff that greet your entrance as soon as they spot you. Attentive and speedy service, huge portions and nice relaxed ambience. Left feeling well looked after and enjoyed this eatery very much indeed.

Solid food, can’t go wrong.
I came in with a sweet tooth and had their chocolate Sunday, oups, ate it before I remember to take a photo, my second course , their pancakes yummy.
Indoor n small outdoor sitting with your dogsss
Very good menu and awesome burgers. Very friendly staff too. One of my favourite places in HK to have lunch.

Good selection of food. Reasonably priced.
Personal favourite is their signature pizza!

Guys, don't go anywhere that has less than 4 stars. 4 is basically average. There is grade inflation on the web!! We didn't check reviews and went on an impulse. Big mistake. My steak and egg was not great. Steak was over cooked (medium well instead of medium rare). And the steak was tiny (not anything near 8oz more like 4oz, see picture). My date ordered a chicken burger which came after 45 mins and they so forgot the fries. OK foods were 3 stars and service was 1 star and I rounded up 2.5 to 3 stars. Basically, skip it!
